                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                                                                Dhoni is Dream XI captain  London: Wisden Wednesday named Virender Sehwag as the Leading Cricketer in the World for 2008 and Mahendra Singh Dhoni captain of its first ever Dream Test XI which includes five Indians.  India rsquo;s rich vein of form found ample reflection in Wisden rsquo;s first ever Dream XI which includes Sehwag, Dhoni, Sachin Tendulkar, Harbhajan Singh and Zaheer Khan.  The Wisden Test XI 2008
  Virender Sehwag, Graeme Smith, Ricky Ponting, Sachin Tendulkar, Kevin Pietersen, Shivnarine Chanderpaul, Mahendra Sing Dhoni, Harbhajan Singh, Mitchell Johnson, Dale Steyn and Zaheer Khan.  Cup qualifiers  Calcutta: The line-up for the Super Eight stage of the ICC World Cup Qualifier was finalised on Wednesday. Defending champions Scotland will be joined by Afghanistan, Ireland, Canada, Namibia, Netherlands, Kenya and the United Arab Emirates. The matches in the Super Eight stage will be starting from Saturday.  Pakistan call  Karachi: Pakistan is all set to call for the formation of an ldquo;Asian Sports Security rdquo; task force at the meeting of sports ministers of Asian countries in May in Tehran. A Pakistan sports ministry official confirmed Wednesday that sports minister, Pir Aftab Shah Jillani will present the proposal in Tehran.  Somdev up  New Delhi: Somdev Dev Varman staged a spirited fightback to beat Korean Davis Cupper Kyu Tae Im 6-7 (4-7), 6-2, 6-2 to move into the second round of the $50,000 ATP Challenger event in Los Angeles.  Meanwhile, Harsh Mankad and American partner Scott Oudsema stunned Thai second-seed Sanchai and Sonchat Ratiwatana 6-4, 6-3 to advance to the quarter finals.   Iraq coach  Baghdad: Iraq rsquo;s Football Association has confirmed it has hired Serbian coach Bora Milutinovic to lead the country rsquo;s national team.  Milutinovic had said Tuesday he had accepted the job to take Iraq to the Confederations Cup in South Africa in June.  Spain No.1  Zurich: Spain continued their domination of Fifa world rankings by establishing a record lead in their 10th straight month at the top. The latest rankings were released on Wednesday.  India, with 156 points, climbed two ranking places to be tied for the No.147th spot with Kyrgyzstan.   World Rankings  1. Spain (1); 2. Germany (2); 3. The Netherlands (3); 4. Brazil (5); 5. Italy (4); 6. Argentina (6); 7. England (9); 8. Croatia (7); 9. Russia (8); 10. France.  Huge loss  London: Portsmouth made losses of pound;16.66 million for the 2007-08 financial year despite winning the FA Cup for the first time in 69 years.  Inquiry  London: An independent inquiry has been commissioned into the finances of Southampton before a decision is made whether the club should be docked points, The English Football League said on Tuesday.  
